claim.claim-text:
1. In a process for producing and spooling preoriented polyester filaments that comprise at least 90 weight % (relative to the total weight of the polyester filaments) polybutylene terephthalate (PBT) and/or polytrimethylene terephthalate (PTMT), the improvement comprising 
(a) mixing the polyester comprising the PBT and/or PTMT with from 0.05 weight % to 2.5 weight % (relative to the total weight of the filament) of a filament elongation-enhancing agent; 
(b) spinning the polyester produced in (a) into filaments through spinning nozzles with a spinline extension-ratio in the range of 70 to 500; 
(c) passing the filaments through a cooling delay zone of from 30 mm to 200 mm in length immediately after exiting from the spinning nozzles; 
(d) cooling the filaments to below the PBT or PTMT solidification temperature; 
(e) bundling the filaments into thread at a distance of between 500 mm and 2500 mm from the spinneret plate; 
(f) setting the thread tension in front of and between draw-off galettes to between 0.05 cN/dtex to 0.20 cN/dtex; 
(g) spooling the thread with a thread tension of between 0.025 cN/dtex to 0.15 cN/dtex and a spooling speed between 2200 m/min. and 6000 m/min.

6. Preoriented polyester filaments wherein after 4 weeks of storage under normal conditions in accordance with DIN 53802, the filaments have the following properties: 
a) an elongation at break between 90 and 165%; 
b) a boiling-water shrinkage of at least 30%; 
c) a normal uster below 1.1%; 
d) a birefringence between 0.030 and 0.058; 
e) a density less than 1.35 g/cm3; 
f) a coefficient of variation of the maximum tensile strength of ≦4.5%; and 
g) a coefficient of variation of the elongation at break of ≦4.5%.
